{"title":"The Winners of the World Dataviz Prize 2023","link":"https://informationisbeautiful.net/2023/the-winners-of-the-world-dataviz-prize-2023/","date":1676461212000,"content":"<p><strong>The results are in! After combing through hundreds of impressive, insightful and inventive entries, we’re proud to announce the winners of the <a href=\"https://wdvp.worldgovernmentsummit.org/\">World Data Visualization Prize 2023</a>.</strong></p>\n<p>Conducted in partnership with the <a href=\"https://www.worldgovernmentsummit.org/\">World Government Summit</a>, the competition this year focuses on the past, present and future of society and governments. We asked entrants to use the power of data-visualization to illuminate data on the innovations, decisions and metrics that can be used to drive and measure progress.</p>\n<p>Scroll through these interactive and static ‘poster’ entries to see who took the grand prize of $25,000.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>Interactive Third Place – $2,500</h1>\n<h2><a href=\"https://palminister.github.io/sustainability-cosmos/\"><strong>Sustainability Cosmos</strong></a></h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos.jpg\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"1103\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos.jpg 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos-480x331.jpg 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos-960x662.jpg 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos-768x529.jpg 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos-1200x827.jpg 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos-240x165.jpg 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-3rd-sustainability-cosmos-1536x1059.jpg 1536w\" /><br />\nThis interactive dashboard uses AI and vivid colours to visualise the sustainability performance of countries based on human, health, environmental, economic, and political conditions. Toggle between different modes to uncover interesting patterns about the current state of our world. By <a href=\"https://supawichorain.myportfolio.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Supawich Orian</a> and <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/palminister/\" target=\"_blank\">Palm Jumnongrat</a></p>\n<h1>Interactive Second Place – $5,000</h1>\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.theshapeofchange.com/\"><strong>The Shape of Change</strong></a></h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change.png\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"1086\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change.png 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change-480x326.png 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change-960x652.png 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change-768x521.png 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change-1200x815.png 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change-240x163.png 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-2nd-shape-of-change-1536x1043.png 1536w\" /><br />\nHooking us with an interactive scrolly-telling guessing game, this playful piece reveals and challenges the assumptions people make around key health, the environment, and education metrics. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/biased_bia\">Beatriz Malveiro</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/_ritacosta_\" target=\"_blank\">Rita Costa</a></p>\n<h1><strong>Interactive Winner $7,500</strong></h1>\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.go4trees.com/four-seasons/\"><strong>Four Seasons: How Has the World Progressed in Recent Years</strong></a><br />\n</h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons.jpg\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"1079\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons.jpg 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons-480x324.jpg 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons-960x647.jpg 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons-768x518.jpg 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons-1200x809.jpg 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons-240x162.jpg 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-1st-four-seasons-1536x1036.jpg 1536w\" /><br />\nThis beautifully elegant visualisation uses the metaphor of a tree in different seasons to spotlight different aspects of progress. Hover over the branches to understand the present, the roots to see the past, and the sky to learn about the future. By <a href=\"http://spark.go4trees.com/\">Liuhuaying Yang</a></p>\n<h2>Honourable Mentions</h2>\n<p>Cited by the judges<br />\n» <strong><a href=\"https://revealthedata.com/dividedworld/\">Divided World</a></strong> (<a href=\"http://revealthedata.com/en/\">Roman Bunin</a>)<br />\n» <strong><a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/sh/j68grcx6m0xzad7/AADEG8aG-ofVAgrshxXixmLca?dl=0\">Globoscope</a></strong> (<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/patrick-obumselu-018411153/?originalSubdomain=ng\">Patrick Obumselu</a>)<br />\n» <strong><a href=\"https://earth-carillon.netlify.app/\">Earth Carillon</a></strong> (<a href=\"http://www.matteopalu.com/\">Matteo Palu</a>)</p>\n<hr />\n<h1><strong>Poster – Joint 3rd Place – $1,000</strong></h1>\n<h2><a>What Just Happened</a>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened.jpg\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"851\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened.jpg 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened-480x255.jpg 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened-960x511.jpg 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened-768x408.jpg 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened-1200x638.jpg 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened-240x128.jpg 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-3rd-what-just-happened-1536x817.jpg 1536w\" /><br />\nThis intriguing, colourful infographic folds in data from NASA, the IPCC, and the World Bank to showcase positive improvements from the last 10-years while also highlighting areas of decline or slow growth. By Jamie Harris and <a href=\"https://linaka.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Linaka Greensword</a></p>\n<h1><strong>Poster – Joint 3rd Place – $1,000</strong></h1>\n<h2><a href=\"https://d33wubrfki0l68.cloudfront.net/5ba77c29-f30f-4918-b909-ea47adae1795/Happy%20People,%20Happy%20Planet.png\">Happy People, Happy Planet</a>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people.png\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"1070\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people.png 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people-480x321.png 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people-960x642.png 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people-768x514.png 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people-1200x803.png 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people-240x161.png 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-4th-happy-people-1536x1027.png 1536w\" /><br />\nDo the countries we traditionally define as the happiest also make our environment happy? And is consumption causing net negative or net positive happiness? This poster addresses these questions with incisive graphics. By Qingyue Li and Enrique Mendoza T.</p>\n<h1><strong>Poster 2nd Place – $3,000</strong></h1>\n<h2><a href=\"https://d33wubrfki0l68.cloudfront.net/09c5ff39-ce75-48fc-84d4-1bda1052b290/WDVP-Emily-Murphy.png\">Report Card for Humanity</a>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card.png\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"870\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card.png 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card-480x261.png 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card-960x522.png 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card-768x418.png 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card-1200x653.png 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card-240x131.png 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-2nd-report-card-1536x835.png 1536w\" /><br />\nThis clarifying infographic challenges the pessimism of progress. By representing change in a “grade” for 5 different categories, you can see what metrics are tending in a positive or negative direction over the last decade. By <a href=\"https://www.emilyjillmurphy.com/data-analytics\">Emily Murphy</a></p>\n<h1><strong>Poster Winner – $5,000</strong></h1>\n<h2><a href=\"https://d33wubrfki0l68.cloudfront.net/58f5bdd4-53ac-4374-9118-7c5e948a3ef7/WDVP_The_light_we_switch_on_03.png\">The Light We Switch On</a>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch.png\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"926\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch.png 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch-480x278.png 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch-960x556.png 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch-768x444.png 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch-1200x695.png 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch-240x139.png 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-poster-1st-light-switch-1536x889.png 1536w\" /><br />\nStark black and white imagery shines a light on electricity and energy consumption and production across the world in a intriguing unfolding journey. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/rafahohr\">Rafael Höhr</a></p>\n<h2>Honourable Mentions</h2>\n<p>Cited by the judges<br />\n» <a href=\"https://d33wubrfki0l68.cloudfront.net/8bdc9c45-47c3-43a2-8911-8173f240006c/World_Data_Visualization_Prize_Submission_SOARES_HARRIS.jpg\"><strong>Leading the Charge to a More Sustainable World</strong></a> (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/marc_soares?lang=en\">Marc Soares</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/nicoleharris222\">Nicole Harris</a>)<br />\n» <a href=\"https://d33wubrfki0l68.cloudfront.net/39e18d5f-2d6d-4ff3-bac8-743abd1a96d1/Nicholas%20Rougeux%20Poster.png\"><strong>Better or Worse</strong></a> (<a href=\"https://www.c82.net/\">Nicholas Rougeux</a>)<br />\n» <a href=\"https://d33wubrfki0l68.cloudfront.net/13ecfaaf-d8c9-4284-ad13-31e5ede4153b/world-viz-raphael-halloran.png\"><strong>Countries with better human development show less corruption and more political freedom</strong></a> (<a href=\"https://www.behance.net/raphaelhalloran\">Raphael Halloran</a>)</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>Grand Prize Winner – $25,000</h1>\n<h2><a href=\"https://lindseypoulter.com/wdvp/\">How do we compare? by Lindsey Poulter</a></h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://infobeautiful4.s3.amazonaws.com/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare.png\" alt width=\"1600\" height=\"1090\" srcset=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare.png 1600w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare-480x327.png 480w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare-960x654.png 960w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare-768x523.png 768w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare-1200x818.png 1200w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare-240x164.png 240w, https://informationisbeautiful.net/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/WDVP-winner-interactive-grand-prize-how-do-we-compare-1536x1046.png 1536w\" /><br />\nThis dynamic,  multi-layered interactive dashboard invites users to focus on an area of interest — an income level, region, or country — and see how it compares to its counterparts across a wide range of metrics. You can randomize the data or choose an individual metric to answer specific questions. Fully explorable data! By <a href=\"https://www.lindseypoulter.com/\">Lindsey Poulter</a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>A massive thank you to our judges, who agonised over the decision-making process – <strong><a href=\"https://albertocairo.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Alberto Cairo</a></strong> a journalist, designer, and scholar who teaches visualization at the University of Miami, <a href=\"https://www.amandamakulec.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Amanda Makulec</strong></a> a data visualization designer and executive director of <a href=\"https://www.datavisualizationsociety.org/\" target=\"_blank\">The Data Visualisation Society</a>, <strong><a href=\"https://www.gurmanbhatia.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Gurman Bhatia</a></strong> an award-winning data journalist based in New Delhi, India, and <strong><a href=\"http://www.davidmccandless.com\">David McCandless</a></strong> founder of Information is Beautiful.</p>\n<p>Massive thanks also to the hundreds who entered. We were seriously impressed by the diversity and incredible creativity of all the entries. We’ll be showcasing a wider selection in the coming weeks.</p>\n<p>In the meantime, you can check out<br />\n» the <a href=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/visualizations/world-dataviz-prize-2023-interactives-longlist/\" target=\"_blank\">interactive longlist</a><br />\n» the <a href=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/visualizations/world-dataviz-prize-2023-poster-longlist/\" target=\"_blank\">poster longlist</a><br />\n» <a href=\"https://informationisbeautiful.net/visualizations/world-dataviz-prize-2023-shortlist/\" target=\"_blank\">the shortlist</a></p>\n<p>Keep an eye out for future dataviz competitions that we run, and maybe consider submitting your work to the <a href=\"https://www.informationisbeautifulawards.com/\">Information is Beautiful Awards</a>, which will launch later this year.</p></h2></h2></h2></h2>","author":"David McCandless","siteTitle":"Information is Beautiful","siteHash":"0e7035277196509eff939ff4c03ce840d3aed5dc63eafcf609568a61850e5f9f","entryHash":"1582b6cd57144f34749d6d6dcf497c13a8f50243187455c03e4de88100a9765f","category":"Tech"}